name: Ocean_DC_IC Functional
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA1/MIL
  Destination - QA1/DEN


  NOTE:

   While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
   In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (BLRTSH2 screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (BLRTSH2 screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa

  Steps:


  1.Process a collect house air shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2.Process a collect house air shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD)
  3.Process EHO shipment to INV
  4. Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.Finish the shipments by printing on BLPRT
  6. Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin
  7.Attach the housebills to a DC destined to a gateway
  8.Print the MNFST
  9.Make sure CFDATA is clear
  10.In Export Origin find on DC reference in DCCOST screen
  11.Enter an amount in the DC Freight Cost and DC Origin Transfer fields., and then hit F1/Post
  12.Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  13.Find on DC reference in gateway DCLOG
  14.Enter DC Destin Cost, and receiving information, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  15.Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  16.Process a new collect ocean house shipment from gateway to destination. Rate and bill in local currency
  17.In gateway consol, attach the original HBLs and a new collect house air shipment to an ICO destined to final destination
  18.Process upto BLPRT screen
  19.Print MNFST
  20.Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  21.Make sure CFDATA is clear
  22.Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

  Data:
  EHO1  collect  VRNDEN (Rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  EHO2  collect  VRN-DEN (Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHO3  collect  MILDEN (Rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  DCO  VRN-MIL
  ICO  MIL-DEN

name: Ocean_GC_DC_IC Functional
description:
House Ocean Shipment (EU to US to CA).  2 EHOs (PPD/COL, 1 w Foreign Currency) traveling on a GC to Gateway1
  A DC to Gateway2, and an ICO to final destination
  Description: Shipment is based on EU to US screen flow.
  EHO1/shipRef1: Currency/EUR (Local), PPD,
  EHO2/shipRef2: Currency/USD (Foreign), COL,
  EHO3/shipref3: Currency/USD (Local) PPD
  EHO4/shipref4: Currency/USD (Local) COL

  Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway1- QA1/DEN
  Gateway2 - QA9/MSY
  Destination - QA4/YYC
  NOTE: 
  While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
  In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa
  Steps:
  1. Process a prepaid house ocean shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2. Process a collect house ocean shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD)
  3. Process EHO shipment to INV
  4. Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5. Finish the shipments by printing on BLPRT
  6.Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin
  7. In Origin consol screen, attach the HBLs to GC destined to gateway1
  8. Process up to MNFST and print
  9. Make sure CFDATA is clear
  10. In Export Origin find on GC reference in DCCOST screen
  11. Enter an amount in the DC Freight Cost and DC Origin Transfer fields., and then hit F1/Post
  12. Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  13. In Export gateway1 find on DC reference in DCLOG screen
  14. Enter DC Destin Cost, and the rest of the fields, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  15. Confirm CFDATA is clear in gateway1
  16. Process a prepaid ocean shipment from gateway1 (DEN) to final destination (YYC). Rate and bill in local currency (USD)
  17. In gateway1 consol, attach the original HBLs and a new prepaid ocean shipment to a DC destined to gateway2
  18. Process upto MNFST and hit F1/Add Modify
  19. In Export gateway1 find on DC reference in DCCOST screen
  20. Enter an amount in the DC Freight Cost and DC Origin Transfer fields., and then hit F1/Post
  21. Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  22. In Export gateway2 find on DC reference in DCLOG screen
  23. Enter DC Destin Cost, and the rest of the fields, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  24. Confirm CFDATA is clear in gateway2
  25. Process a new collect ocean house shipment from gateway2 (MSY) to destination YYC. Rate and bill in local currency, USD
  26. In gateway2 consol, attach all 4 HB shipment to an ICO destined to final destination
  27. Process upto BLPRT screen
  28. Print MNFST
  29. Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  30. Make sure CFDATA is clear
  31. Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

name: Ocean_IC_DC_IC Functional
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway1- QA1/DEN
  Gateway2 - QA9/MSY
  Destination - QA4/YYC

  Steps:
  1.	Process a prepaid house air shipment from origin VRN to final destination YYC. Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2.	Process a prepaid house air shipment from origin VRN to final destination YYC. Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  3.	Process EHO shipment to INV
  4.	 Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5.	Finish the shipments by printing on BLPRT
  6.	 Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin VRN
  7.	Attach the housebills to an IC destined to gateway1 DEN
  8.	Print the MNFST
  9.	Post MCTRAN
  10.	Find on IC reference in CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  11.	Receive ShipLog at gateway1 (DEN) CFIT and post the consol settlement
  12.	Receive ShipLog at final destination (YYC) CFIT and post the consol settlement
  13.	Find on origin IC reference in gateway1 DEN DCLOG screen
  14.	Enter receiving information and hit F1/Add Modify
  15.	Find on IC references in gateway1 DEN CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  16.	Process a prepaid house ocean shipment from gateway1 DEN to final destination YYC. Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  17.	In gateway1 DEN consol, attach the original HBLs and a new collect house ocean shipment to an DC destined to gateway2 MSY
  18.	Process upto MNFST and hit F1/Add Modify
  19.	In Export gateway1 find on DC reference in DCCOST screen (I believe Next Screen from step #18 above will lead you to DCCOST screen)
  20.	Enter an amount in the DC Freight Cost and DC Origin Transfer fields, and then hit F1/Post
  21.	Find on DC reference in CFDATA, and make sure it is clear
  22.	In Export gateway2 MSY find on DC reference in DCLOG screen
  23.	Enter DC Destin Cost, and the rest of the fields, and then hit F1/Add Modify
  24.	Confirm CFDATA is clear in gateway2 MSY
  25.	Process a new prepaid ocean house shipment from gateway2 MSY to final destination YYC. Rate and bill in local currency (USD)
  26.	In gateway2 MSY consol, attach all 4 HB shipment to an ICO destined to final destination YYC
  27.	Process upto BLPRT screen
  28.	Print MNFST
  29.	Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  30.	Make sure CFDATA is clear
  31.	Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

  Data:
  EHO1  prepaid  VRNYYC (Rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  EHO2  prepaid  VRN-YYC (Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  ICO  VRN-DEN
  Link EHO1, EHO2 to ICO1
  Receive ShipLog at gateway1 (DEN) CFIT and post the consol settlement
  Receive ShipLog at final destination (YYC) CFIT and post the consol settlement

  EHO3  prepaid  DEN-YYC (Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  DCO1  DEN-MSY
  Link EHO1, EHO2, EHO3 to DCO1

  EHO4  prepaid  MSY-YYC (Rate and bill in local currency (USD))
  ICO2  MSY-YYC
  Link EHO1, EHO2, EHO3 and EHO4 to ICO2
  Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

name: Ocean_B2B_IC_MCCOST
description:
Create an end-to-end automation script for the Ocean back to back shipment scenario along with Origin Consol corrections and validating accounting transactions.

  Process 1 prepaid and 1 collect shipment

  
  Post MCTRAN at Origin Export
  For Prepaid
  Verify II
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin CFIT - AR History by Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Verify ES
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  
  For Collect
  Verify HCII
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin CFIT - AR History by Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Verify ES
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  
  Post Consol Settlement at Destination CFIT
  For Prepaid
  Verify CSII
  Destination CFIT - AR History By Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Destination EIFA - Review Journal and Expect all contents are correct
  Verify CSRI
  CFIT Origin - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents are correct
  
  For Collect
  Verify HCRI
  CFIT Destination - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Destination - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Verify CSII
  Destination CFIT - AR History By Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Destination EIFA - Review Journal and Expect all contents are correct
  Verify CSRI
  CFIT Origin - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents are correc
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Go back to Export Origin and perform Origin Correction
  For Housebill 1
  Export Origin - ICCOST - user should be changing all editable fields: Airport Transfer, Dest Fee Description and Dest Fee (reduce all editable amount)
  Export Origin - HBCOST - user will be in shipRef1 (housebill 1) and updating onforwarding HdLg Gee and CFS Fee
  Post MCTRAN
  Verify ESafter correction and posting MCTRAN
  Origin CFIT - Pay from Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Origin EIFA - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Verify CSRM
  CFIT Origin - Review Vendor Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents are correct
  Verify CSIM
  Destination CFIT - Review Invoice and Expect all the contents are correct
  Destination EIFA - Review Journal and Expect all contents are correct

  Cancel/Rebill - ShipRef1
  If ShipRef = Prepaid
  Add another line item to the latest suffix say suffix 03
  Post INV
  Post MCTRAN
  Verify XI, II
  CFIT Origin - AR History by Invoice
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal
  Verify ES
  CFIT Origin - Pay from Invoice
  CFIT EIFA - Review Journal
  Verify CSXI, II
  CFIT Origin - AR History by Invoice
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal
  Verify CSRI
  CFIT Destination - Review Vendor Invoice
  EIFA Destination - Review Journal
  
  Else if Cancel/Rebill = Collect Invoice
  Add another line item to the latest suffix say suffix 03
  Post INV
  Verify XI, II
  CFIT Origin
  EIFA Origin
  Verify ES
  CFIT Origin - Pay From Invoice and Expect all the contents
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents
  Verify HCXII, II
  CFIT Origin - AR History by Invoice and Expect all the contents
  EIFA Origin - Review Journal and Expect all the contents
  Verify HCRI, RM
  CFIT Destination - Review Vendor Invoice

  EIFA Destination - Review Journal
